---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="MCP Server Setup" description="Set up coverit as an MCP server for Claude Code and other AI tools.">
  <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-text">MCP Server Setup</h1>

  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Coverit works as an <a href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MCP (Model Context Protocol)</a>
    server. This means AI tools like Claude Code can use coverit's capabilities directly through
    a standardized protocol, without you running CLI commands manually.
  </p>

  <!-- What is MCP -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">What is MCP?</h2>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open standard that allows AI assistants to use
    external tools. When coverit runs as an MCP server, the AI can call coverit's functions
    directly &mdash; scanning your codebase, generating tests, and fixing failures without
    you copying commands back and forth.
  </p>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    This is the recommended way to use coverit with Claude Code. The AI orchestrates the
    entire workflow: scanning, identifying gaps, writing tests, running them, and reporting results.
  </p>

  <!-- Auto setup -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">Automatic setup</h2>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The easiest way to configure MCP is to run the setup wizard:
  </p>
  <pre class="bg-bg-code text-[#f5f0e8] font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>npx @devness/coverit</code></pre>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    This detects your installed AI tools (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, Cursor, Windsurf, etc.) and
    configures the MCP server for each one automatically. No manual JSON editing required.
  </p>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    You can also run the setup wizard explicitly:
  </p>
  <pre class="bg-bg-code text-[#f5f0e8] font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>npx @devness/coverit mcp</code></pre>

  <!-- Manual configuration -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">Manual configuration</h2>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    If you prefer to configure manually, add the following to your MCP configuration file.
  </p>

  <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3 text-text">Claude Desktop</h3>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Add to <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">claude_desktop_config.json</code>:
  </p>
  <pre class="bg-bg-code text-[#f5f0e8] font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>&#123;
  "mcpServers": &#123;
    "coverit": &#123;
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@devness/coverit@latest"]
    &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3 text-text">Claude Code</h3>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Add to <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">.mcp.json</code> in your project root:
  </p>
  <pre class="bg-bg-code text-[#f5f0e8] font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>&#123;
  "mcpServers": &#123;
    "coverit": &#123;
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@devness/coverit@latest"]
    &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

  <!-- MCP Tools -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">MCP tools</h2>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Once configured, the following 7 tools become available to the AI:
  </p>
  <table class="w-full border-collapse mb-6">
    <thead>
      <tr class="bg-bg-warm">
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left font-body font-semibold text-sm">Tool</th>
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left font-body font-semibold text-sm">Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-mono text-sm">coverit_scan</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-body text-sm">AI scans and analyzes the codebase, creates <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">coverit.json</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-mono text-sm">coverit_cover</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-body text-sm">Generates tests from gaps, runs them, fixes failures, updates score</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-mono text-sm">coverit_run</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-body text-sm">Runs existing tests, fixes failures via AI, rescans and updates score</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-mono text-sm">coverit_status</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-body text-sm">Shows the quality dashboard from <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">coverit.json</code> (instant, no AI)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-mono text-sm">coverit_clear</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-body text-sm">Deletes <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">coverit.json</code> and <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">.coverit/</code> for a fresh start</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-mono text-sm">coverit_backup</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-body text-sm">Exports <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">coverit.json</code> as a portable backup</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-mono text-sm">coverit_restore</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-body text-sm">Imports <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">coverit.json</code> from a backup</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Each tool accepts a <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">projectRoot</code>
    parameter &mdash; the absolute path to the project being analyzed.
  </p>

  <!-- Claude Code plugin -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">Claude Code plugin</h2>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    For Claude Code, the recommended approach is the plugin. It bundles the MCP server
    with slash commands and CLAUDE.md instructions &mdash; all in one step:
  </p>
  <pre class="bg-bg-code text-[#f5f0e8] font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>/plugin marketplace add devness-com/coverit
/plugin install coverit@coverit</code></pre>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The plugin provides both the MCP tools above and the following slash commands.
  </p>

  <!-- Slash commands -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">Slash commands</h2>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    When using coverit as a Claude Code plugin, you get convenient slash commands:
  </p>
  <table class="w-full border-collapse mb-6">
    <thead>
      <tr class="bg-bg-warm">
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left font-body font-semibold text-sm">Command</th>
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left font-body font-semibold text-sm">Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-mono text-sm">/coverit:scan</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-body text-sm">AI scans and analyzes codebase, creates <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">coverit.json</code>, shows dashboard</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-mono text-sm">/coverit:cover</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-body text-sm">AI generates tests from gaps, shows before/after score</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-mono text-sm">/coverit:run</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-body text-sm">Runs existing tests, AI fixes failures</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-mono text-sm">/coverit:status</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-body text-sm">Shows quality dashboard from <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">coverit.json</code></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Slash commands are the quickest way to use coverit. Just type the command in Claude Code
    and the AI handles everything &mdash; delegating to a sub-agent for heavy work and reporting
    results back to you.
  </p>

  <!-- How it works -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">How it works</h2>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    When coverit runs as an MCP server, the flow is different from standalone CLI usage:
  </p>
  <ul class="ml-6 list-disc mb-4">
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">
      <strong>No external AI provider needed</strong> &mdash; the AI tool (Claude Code) is
      itself the AI. Coverit doesn't need to call out to any separate provider.
    </li>
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">
      <strong>Direct tool access</strong> &mdash; the AI can read files, search code, and run
      commands directly through its own tool capabilities.
    </li>
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">
      <strong>Conversational context</strong> &mdash; the AI has full context of your
      conversation, so it can make smarter decisions about what to test and how.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    When you invoke <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">npx @devness/coverit</code>
    in a non-TTY (piped) context, it automatically starts the MCP server. In a TTY (terminal)
    context, it runs the setup wizard instead.
  </p>

  <!-- Troubleshooting -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">Troubleshooting</h2>

  <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3 text-text">MCP server not detected</h3>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    If your AI tool doesn't see the coverit MCP tools, try:
  </p>
  <ul class="ml-6 list-disc mb-4">
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">Re-run the setup wizard: <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">npx @devness/coverit</code></li>
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">Restart your AI tool (Claude Code, Cursor, etc.) to reload MCP configurations</li>
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">Verify <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">.mcp.json</code> exists in your project root with the correct configuration</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3 text-text">Tools time out</h3>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The scan and cover operations use AI to explore your codebase, which can take several
    minutes for large projects. If tools are timing out:
  </p>
  <ul class="ml-6 list-disc mb-4">
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">Ensure you have a stable internet connection (for cloud-based providers)</li>
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">For very large codebases, use <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">targetPaths</code> in your config to limit scope</li>
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">Run the CLI version instead: <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">npx @devness/coverit scan</code></li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
